  "prompt": "Where can I study at Stanford?",
  "response": "At Stanford University, you have a variety of options for studying, depending on your interests and academic goals. Here are some key locations and resources on campus:\n\n1. **Main Library**: The Stanford University Libraries system includes the Green Library, which is the main library, and numerous specialized libraries. It's a great place for research and study.\n\n2. **Study Rooms**: Many buildings on campus have study rooms that can be reserved or used on a first-come, first-served basis. Look into the study spaces in the libraries and academic buildings.\n\n3. **Academic Departments**: Each academic department has its own facilities and study spaces. Depending on your major, you might find dedicated study areas in those departments.\n\n4. **The Stanford Center for Teaching and Learning**: This center offers resources and support for students, including tutoring and study groups.\n\n5. **The Graduate School of Business**: For those studying business, the GSB has its own facilities and study areas tailored for its students.\n\n6. **The School of Engineering**: If you're in engineering, there are specific labs and study spaces designed to support engineering students.\n\n7. **Common Areas**: Many dorms and student centers have common areas where students can study, collaborate, or socialize.\n\n8. **Outdoor Spaces**: Stanford's beautiful campus also offers outdoor areas that can be conducive to studying, especially in pleasant weather.\n\n9. **Student Centers**: The Student Center and other student-run spaces often provide areas for group study and collaboration.\n\nMake sure to check availability and specific guidelines for each location, especially during busy times like midterms and finals.",
